{
  "doc_id": "27773",
  "text": "Cell adhesion to a biomaterial surface is a complex and dynamic process. Macromolecular complexes in serum play a role in mediating the material surface to extracellular matrix [CITATION_1] . MWCNTs have high protein-absorption ability [CITATION_2] . Various kinds of proteins involved in the serum would affect the chemical property of the MWCNT-coated surface. In order to estimate the effect of proteins in the serum, a serum-free culture was carried out. In spite of the serum-free culture, a significantly larger number of cells were attached to the center part of the MWCNT-coated sponge than to the collagen sponge.",
